<section class=3D"section main-article-chapter" data-menu-title=3D"What is =
a binary formula?">
 <h2 class=3D"section-title"><i class=3D"icon" data-icon=3D"1"></i>What is =
a binary formula?</h2>
 <p>A binary formula is a formula that's used to convert binary numbers to =
decimal, duodecimal or hexadecimal numbers. The formula is different for di=
fferent conversions.</p>
 <p>To convert a binary number to decimal form:</p>
 <ul class=3D"default-list">=20
  <li>Every digit of the number is multiplied by 2 raised to the power of t=
hat digit's position in the number.</li>=20
  <li>The results of the multiplications for each digit are added together.=
</li>=20
 </ul>
 <p>Consider a binary number B =3D b<sub>n-1</sub>=E2=80=A6.b<sub>3</sub>b<=
sub>2</sub>b<sub>1</sub>b<sub>0</sub>. Here's how the binary formula will l=
ook:</p>
 <p>For B =3D b<sub>n-1</sub>=E2=80=A6.b<sub>3</sub>b<sub>2</sub>b<sub>1</s=
ub>b<sub>0</sub></p>
 <p>D =3D (b<sub>n-1</sub> =C3=97 2<sup>n-1</sup>) +=E2=80=A6+(b<sub>3</sub=
> =C3=97 2<sup>3</sup>) + (b<sub>2</sub> =C3=97 2<sup>2</sup>) + (b<sub>1</=
sub> =C3=97 2<sup>1</sup>) + (b<sub>0</sub> =C3=97 2<sup>0</sup>)</p>
 <p>Suppose B =3D (1101011)<sub>2</sub></p>
 <p>Here,</p>
 <p>n =3D 7</p>
 <p>n - 1 =3D 6</p>
 <p>D =3D (1 =C3=97 2<sup>6</sup>) +(1 =C3=97 2<sup>5</sup>) + (0 =C3=97 2<=
sup>4</sup>) + (1 =C3=97 2<sup>3</sup>) + (0 =C3=97 2<sup>2</sup>)+ (1 =C3=
=97 2<sup>1</sup>) + (1 =C3=97 2<sup>0</sup>)</p>
 <p>=3D 64 + 32 + 0 + 8 + 0 + 2 + 1</p>
 <p>D =3D 107</p>
 <p>Thus, (1101011)<sub>2 </sub>=3D (107)<sub>10</sub></p>
 <p>The formula for converting binary to hexadecimal and octal numbers is m=
uch less straightforward and can be tedious to do manually.</p>
</section>               =20
