<section class=3D"section main-article-chapter" data-menu-title=3D"Applicat=
ions of binary">
 <h2 class=3D"section-title"><i class=3D"icon" data-icon=3D"1"></i>Applicat=
ions of binary</h2>
 <p>The binary number system is used in other areas, such as email communic=
ation, <a href=3D"https://www.techtarget.com/searchstorage/definition/compr=
ession">data compression</a> systems and data <a href=3D"https://www.techta=
rget.com/searchsecurity/definition/encryption">encryption</a>. Cryptographi=
cal systems use binary code to transform <a href=3D"https://www.techtarget.=
com/searchsecurity/definition/plaintext">plaintext</a> data into unreadable=
 <a href=3D"https://www.techtarget.com/whatis/definition/ciphertext">cipher=
text</a>. Compressing data into binary form reduces its size so it requires=
 less storage space.</p>
 <p>Binary information is also used in digital <a href=3D"https://www.techt=
arget.com/whatis/definition/audio">audio</a> and <a href=3D"https://www.tec=
htarget.com/whatis/definition/digital-video">video</a> processing. Applicat=
ions encode audio and video files as digital data in binary form. To enable=
 playback, the data is decoded into analog form.</p>
 <p>Artificial intelligence (<a href=3D"https://www.techtarget.com/searchen=
terpriseai/definition/AI-Artificial-Intelligence">AI</a>) and machine learn=
ing (<a href=3D"https://www.techtarget.com/searchenterpriseai/definition/ma=
chine-learning-ML">ML</a>) applications also use binary data. These include=
 language translation and <a href=3D"https://www.techtarget.com/searchenter=
priseai/definition/image-recognition">image recognition</a> apps.</p>
 <p><i>Network admins should know how to convert binary to decimal and vice=
 versa for IPv4 addressing, subnet masks, default gateways, and network IDs=
. Learn </i><a href=3D"https://www.techtarget.com/searchnetworking/tip/Bina=
ry-to-decimal-conversion"><i>how to convert binary to decimal</i></a><i>.</=
i></p>
</section></section>









